div.p:
This study should examine policy towards COCOM, U.S. differential controls, trade with Eastern
                            Europe, Asian communist and Cuban trade embargos, and extraterritorial
                            effects of trade controls, by treating the following elements: 

—the effectiveness of present measures;

—the strategic impact of these controls upon communist
                                    countries;

—relations with our allies;

—other relevant factors including U.S. exports, our balance of
                                    payments and relations between the U.S. Government, on the one
                                    hand, and U.S. business and labor, on the other.
